<Pics>None< /Pics>< Review>
This is a cute neighborhood park. There is a large field with soccer goals, basketball courts, 2 wonderful shaded playgrounds, and a BBQ area you can rent out for small family gatherings. The huge drawback is the lack of a restroom facility, as well as there is no fence along the boarders near the main road leading out of the small community. They do have 2 porta potties along the main road, which I think they should leave near the BBQ area for safety.</Review>

I‚Äôve been a customer here for almost 5 years. I‚Äôve watched this store turn around through innovative transformations and changing with the times especially post pandemic to meet customer needs and ensuring public safety. I haven‚Äôt met anyone as knowledgeable about reptile, fish, birds, and animal care in general then the Stores owner Ron. Animals are taken care of daily, customers are put first with great deals on products that meet specific needs for easy to advanced care animals. Tails2scales has just about everything you need to take care of almost any pet you could own. I buy my cat food, feeder insects in many varieties, live feeders like mice and rats to feed my snakes, calcium and vitamin supplements for my reptiles, heat and lighting, caging, and of coarse some amazing exotic animals. < Name>
Alison</Name>
<Date>1595369538652</Date><Rate>2</Rate>< text>
If you buy live food from them (mice, crickets, roaches etc.) Either bring your own clear container or ask to see inside the bag before they staple it closed. They have given me bags where more crickets were dead than alive, or if they have a shortage they don't tell me, give me what they do have (which are half dead typically)  and then still charge me for what I originally asked for. If the owner isn't there and you have questions about stuff, don't bother talking to the people that work there because they know as little as you do about the animals. I've asked for pinkies before and they've given me fuzzies or larger and I don't know until I've already driven home and then can't return them because they have a no return policy (hence why you ask to see inside the bag before they staple it closed and give it to you).
The owner does have a really good variety of snakes and reptiles a lot of the time which is cool and is pretty good at giving great deals when it comes to buying pets, but other than that I don't plan on buying live food from them anytime soon.</text>

< Review>
Always a good time coming in to this shop. My husband and I have dogs, fish, and an African grey. They also have some of the better prices ive seen around town. The ice cream at Creamistry is absolutely amazing! The liquid nitrogen is a bit of a gimmick, but it provides a cool atmosphere (no pun intended) and the final result is incredibly smooth and creamy. They also have a deal going on where you can get 10% off if you check in on Facebook or Yelp, and another 10% off another serving if you bring back your receipt within a week. This place is very expensive, but I think it's worth it. (I reccomend the salted caramel)<//review>

<Date>1567175850648</Date>< text>
Great ice cream shop with 5-6 ice cream makers on the counter behind the glass dividers where you can watch your ice cream being made.

Walked in in a warm Saturday night, store was staffed with 6 teens running the shop. There was only one person ahead of us. We ordered a scoop of coffee ice cream ($5.50 for a regular size) and a spicy mango ice cream fruit cup (A whopping $9.95). The coffee ice cream was just perfect, rich creamy and flavorful. The mango was definitely for an acquired taste. It was a strange flavor with the extra spicy pepper powder on top.

The staff was definitely trying to do their best, but couldn't help noticing how they were in a state of chaos at times. No older supervisor was present at least when we were there...

I would consider them in future for a regular size of an ice cream scoop like the coffee flavored one I had. Paying almost $10 for the cup with fruits was definitely way over what it was worth....</text>
<username>Mehrnaz Horraw</username>< user>

<pictures>None</pictures>< text>
We went here spontaneously after dinner.  I know this is a chain but it's the first one we have ever been to.  The technique they use to make the ice cream is quite exciting and a great visual, but I thought "oh that's all this place is about".  Boy was I ever wrong. Who knew making ice cream this way will produce the most creamy ice cream I ever had.  Literary NO ice crystals were present in the ice cream.  I think it might have been the best ice cream I ever had.  Definitely will be back!  Go... It will change you thoughts about what makes good ice cream.< /text>

<user_id>114737315479666556303< /user_id>< Name>
Y A</Name>
<time>1569936253818</time><rate>5< /rate>< text>
They make the ice cream here on the spot. Meaning, when you walk in, they start with cream and using liquid nitrogen they make it into ice cream in front of your eyes. They claim this process makes the ice cream creamier and it really does! The ice cream itself was delicious. The toppings and how they pair different flavours of ice cream with different toppings was genius. It's like a geekier Baskin Robbins and sooo delicious. It's definitely our new favourite ice cream place now!<//text>

<user>112251132045797567991</user><name>Tommy Grahn</name><Date>1412707409728<//Date><rate>5</rate><review>We purchased our hot tub from Creative Energy in San Mateo almost 10 years ago and it's still one of the best purchases we've ever made.   The tub is in use almost every night and aside from minimal maintenance we haven't had any major problems with it.  Works like a charm.   I can't tell you the relief from stress I get when I first sit in the tub.   I can feel the stress and pains from the day just leave my body.   It's the most wonderful sensation and I recommend it for everyone.  I feel so lucky to have my hot tub and I'm glad I bought it from Creative Energy.

We recently returned to the store to pick up supplies and we were interested in the fireplace inserts as our wood burning fireplace was giving us trouble.    We ended up buying one on the spot due mostly to their wonderfully helpful sales staff and their great selection of units in their showroom.  We had all of them going full blast to do comparisons and boy that room heated up quickly.    Here it is almost a month later and we are so in love with our new fireplace.   We can turn it on with the push a button on the remote and instantly have a huge, warm fire in the living room.  It's fantastic!    I also love the temperature control on the remote.   Just set it to the temperature that you want and it turns the fireplace on and off to maintain that temperature.   Just fantastic!

I have to say I wasn't a big fan of gas fireplaces and wanted to keep my wood burning one but after seeing how easy they are to operate and how nice they look I was hooked.    We got the one that has big roundish stones instead of the fake log and it looks fantastic!  Very modern and sleek.    WE LOVE IT!

UPDATE:

I am totally happy with Creative Energy and this is why....  i bought my hot tub from their San Mateo showroom 11 years ago and have used it almost every night since then.   I have never had a bad experience dealing with their customer service and I've had them out to service minor repairs several times over the years.   I also purchased a gas insert to replace my wood burning fireplace several years ago and have been using that a lot.   The fireplace stopped working last week so I scheduled an appointment to have it serviced and got an appointment quickly scheduled.   Then I thought I would try and combine that fireplace service with some minor things that were not working in the hot tub since they came from the same company.  I didn't really expect that they would send one person to do both servicing as they are completely different equipment but they said Dave would be coming out and he is an expert.

I had a appointment scheduled for 9am last Friday and I was a little freaked out because I had a wedding to attend that day at 1pm and wasn't sure that both appliances would be fixed in time for me to leave for the wedding.   Dave was so efficient and worked quickly and got me to the wedding on time.   I couldn't believe he actually took the whole fireplace apart and (luckily for me I was still in the warranty time period for the fireplace so I didn't have to pay for the two parts he replaced) got it put back together in a couple of hours.    This was still getting close to my cutoff time but he went to work on the hot tub and got that done in plenty of time for me to make the wedding.

I can't give enough props to Dave Kirley and his skill set.   He is very knowledgeable in how these machines work and did a really superb job in fixing mine.   Now I feel like I'm in a new hot tub even though it's 11 years old!   And I can enjoy my fireplace again which is now working perfectly!     Kudos to Dave and his team (the customer support people on the phone were very helpful and accommodated me in my last minute request to get both appliances serviced).    I am very happy with Creative Energy and would recommend them to anybody interested in either a hot tub or fireplace fixture.</review>< pics>

<time>1377830010281< /time>< Name>
Annie Bananie< /Name>
<text>In the past (and hopefully in the future), I would have given Rancho Huntington Mobile Home Estates five gold stars. However, in the recent past the park has been purchased by a large corporation that is attempting to change us over from a senior park to an all-age park. As many of our neighbors did, we purchased our mobile home with the intention of living here until we died and leaving our home to our son and his family. The management company has not made any attempt to resolve this situation or even discuss it with the current residents. This is long been a quiet and serene mobile home park where many members of Orange County s older community have been happy to spend their retirement years. With the possibility of families with children moving into the park, the quiet enjoyment of our park, including the swimming pool, the billiards room, the workout room, the laundry facilities, etc. will be lost. There will be a lot of noise and children riding bicycles, skateboards, roller skates, and other children s toys throughout the days. Those who are disabled and/or sick will not be able to relax and take a nap in the afternoon. Huntington Beach City Council is attempting to assist the residents in their attempt to keep RHMHEs a senior park, but only time will tell.< /text><Rating>3< /Rating>< userid>
103386702212784699285< /userid>

<Date>1566753496260< /Date><rating>5</rating><text>Growing up in NYC, I like to think I appreciate a good cheesesteak, and let me tell you - this place makes a GREAT one!

Went in for a quick lunch and left feeling I had made new friends. Incredibly friendly owners that really care about what they are serving you and it shows in the food.

Had a steak with provolone (no whiz for me, thankyouverymuch) with all the veggies and they put it on an amazing Amoroso roll. So many places will make a good sandwich and then put it on a sub-par roll, ruining it. Not these guys. They go the extra mile to bring the Amoroso's in and it's worth it.

Wife is a vegetarian, but got some cheesefries with all the veggies they put on the sandwich and she loved it. Totally filled her up too.

Finished them off with a Franks vanilla creme soda and a Pennsylvania Dutch birch beer (ah childhood memories!).

Great place, great food, great people.
I will be back!</text><pictures>None<//pictures>< Resp>

< Review>
In the internet age there is no shortage of places to satisfy any type of craving. This does not mean you will like every place you find though. Well, I‚Äôm happy to say Steak N Fries did not disappoint. I had a craving for a good cheesesteak and the usual places were already closed. Did a quick search and found this place. I called and spoke to Angel, the owner. It started with the treatment I received on the phone. Angel was friendly and answered my questions without rushing me off the phone. I said we would stop by and we did. Mind you, the restaurant is in Pacific Beach, and we were coming from East County. Totally worth the drive. Upon arrival, I was greeted by Angel who not only remembered speaking with me, but went out of his way to be welcoming. He explained everything about the menu and was patient while my kids ordered. The restaurant only has a couple of small tables, but Angel again went out of his way to set up seating. The cheesesteak was excellent. They use thinly sliced (fresh daily) ribeye meat which is tender, not over cooked, and delicious. You have your choice of cheese, to include the traditional Cheese Whiz, along with Swiss, American, provolone, and mozzarella. I highly recommend the Loaded Cheesesteak, which comes with fries on top. Great food, great service. Way to run a business!<//Review>

< Review>
I have been coming to Sam Ash since I was a kid. The service has always been just ok, but the staff is nice enough. Right now they are under staffed due to Covid. The part that is less forgivable is the selection of guitars is boring. Most are messed up some how or at least out of tune. They haven't renovated since they opened so it is starting to look out dates and run down.
If you are going to get general music stuff it's a great place to go, and I'm sure they will have what your looking for!< /Review>

<user>112627205776797802118</user><username>Maxwell Hallwachs</username><Date>1510167631216< /Date>< Rating>
2< /Rating>
< Review>
It's hard to say I like this location. The only times I've ever had a good experience at the store, I was only browsing. The times I've made purchases, I struggled to find a representative to help me make a transaction.

Most recently I went in to buy a case for my guitar, which is a reverse fender offset body style, so I just wanted someone to help me find a case that fit. Of course, the only people I can find are either busy or walking away from me and pick up the pace when they hear me say excuse me. I'd gone to the greeter and asked if he could help me and his response was something along the lines of "sorry I can't help I'm just a greeter." Really? Where I work, if I can't answer a question or I can't help someone, I find someone who can. That's customer service. I ask if he can call someone over the intercom to help me, and he would say "yeah I can definitely do that for you. .....did you want me to do that right now? You want me to call someone to come here?" Im just thinking, Buddy, are you stupid? He called someone for me and I spoke with them for a bit, he told me to wait where I was while he pulled out a case to see if it fit. 10 minutes pass and I see him helping another guest so I opted to wait in line at the register and asked the cashier to help me. Cashier calls someone else, which is understandable because there were customers behind me in line that needed to complete a purchase. The guy pulls out a case and it's not the right fit, then he pulls out another case that fit and when he was ringing me up he told me the keys to lock the case were inside the compartment under where the neck would sit. I go home relieved that I finally was done with the situation. A little excited I have a new case for my guitar, I'm checking it out a little closer and realize the keys were nowhere to be found. This place already gave me bad enough service, I don't want to go back and deal with the same workers and get treated the same way again. I genuinely felt as though my time and money was of no value to this location.

However, I have had some good experiences at this location when I'm just browsing. I'll be looking at microphones or effects pedals and a rep will strike up conversation with me. Just casual conversation, it doesn't feel like they just want to make a sale, it feels like they genuinely want to talk to me about what they're saying. Some of their representative are very well informed and know what they're talking about, and they are very polite and cordial. Where are these reps when I actually intend to make a purchase?

I don't plan on making any purchases here again any time soon. I shouldn't have to come on a "good day" or hope one of the "good workers" is available to help me out. Would not recommend this location.< /Review>

<Text>I have not been to this location in years but I am looking for a specific seven string guitar. I thought I would give it an other showlt since I haven't had luck at other places.

First thing, don't expect anyone to ask how you are doing or if you need help. I was there for almost an hour and not one employee said anything to me. People play waaay to loud and employees don't say anything. I get that you want to try out amps but there is no reason to have two people playing at level 10.  I saw a few guitars with broken or missing strings. Because it is in a mall, you get a lot of different people that would never be in a music store -- this could explain the broken stings.

The only good thing about this place is that they have a bigger selection of guitars then Guitar Center in Rancho Cucamonga. That being said, the negatives don't out weight the positive. I am sure other Sam Ash locations are better then this one but I was disappointed that it hasn't changed after all these years.</Text>< rating>

<Text>It was great as always going into Sam Ash, I have shopped at this same location at Ontario Mills for about 3-4 times. I felt that this location needed to have a little more customer service where the keyboards are, and someone with great knowledge of software should be by the mics and software at all times. All 3-4 times I shopped there , there was no one there that could give me any answers, one time the salesman for mics and gadgets, software was on lunch. All 3 of us customers had to walk away because we waited so long, the salesmen from the drum section had to help I me.
Besides that, Sam Ash has the best prices , compared to online stores such as Sweetwater and more.
Smile more guys, jump in to help those around the store a little more aggressive, it's a walk way right through to the mall, you got a great opportunities to gain more customers, take advantage of it, offer them flyers and let them know you have deals! Because I walked straight through that place, and not one person asked about my experience there.

<review>I usually shop at a different major musical instrument store that is just a few miles from my house, but when they didn't have what I was looking for, I called Sam Ash.  I called in to see if they had some drumheads I needed. <user_id>117784593800511535023< /user_id>< response>

<Pictures>None</Pictures><rating>2<//rating>< review>
DO NOT ORDER gear from the store unless it is either on display or actually available. I ordered a 1984 Goth Epiphone Explorer early January and didn't get it till late March. The reason for this is that everytime they ordered it, it either came in terribly scratched or obviously used. They ordered it three times from different Sam Ash stores and all were in bad condition. They then ordered it directly from the factory(took literally about a month to arrive) and even that one had bad scratches. Finally the fifth guitar came in from the factory and it had very minor scratches on the bottom edge of the guitar, but I just kept it because it was in the best condition out of all of them. Never ordering gear from here again.
The service was good though. I'd rate 5 stars if it wasn't for all this crap that happened.

TL;DR Order gear from guitar center :)</review>

<review>I ordered $6 worth of Pearl Drum parts on December 4th. When I placed the order, I was told it would take 7 to 10 working days. The order wasn't placed until the 9th of December. After calling Sam Ash numerous times over the past month to determine where the parts are, I finally spoke with Pearl Drums and FedEx, the shipper. FedEx says that the package was lost. There is now a case number for the lost package. Pearl Drums will not sell the parts (2 bolts and 2 wingnuts) to me directly. They will only sell through music stores. They are now going to follow-up with FedEx with the Case Number I provided them. In the whole process, not one person has been proactive or concerned about the order. I know it was December (near Christmas and Hanukkah) and I know that it was only a $6 order. Regardless, the customer service has been non-existent at Sam Ash, Pearl Drums, or FedEx. I am going to do what I should have done in the first place and that is to go to the hardware store to find similar bolts and wingnuts. I wanted to use all Pearl Drum parts on the Pearl Bass Drum stand on which the parts go but am finding out that it is not worth it.

I will never purchase anything from Sam Ash again. That goes for the large purchases I usually make of PA gear, cymbals, guitars and accessories, microphones, drums and drum accessories. I will go out of my way and pay more elsewhere. They don't deserve my business. They certainly haven't earned it.<//review>< Pics>

<review>I ordered $6 worth of Pearl Drum parts on December 4th. When I placed the order, I was told it would take 7 to 10 working days. The order wasn't placed until the 9th of December. After calling Sam Ash numerous times over the past month to determine where the parts are, I finally spoke with Pearl Drums and FedEx, the shipper. FedEx says that the package was lost. There is now a case number for the lost package. Pearl Drums will not sell the parts (2 bolts and 2 wingnuts) to me directly. They will only sell through music stores. They are now going to follow-up with FedEx with the Case Number I provided them. In the whole process, not one person has been proactive or concerned about the order. I know it was December (near Christmas and Hanukkah) and I know that it was only a $6 order. Regardless, the customer service has been non-existent at Sam Ash, Pearl Drums, or FedEx. I am going to do what I should have done in the first place and that is to go to the hardware store to find similar bolts and wingnuts. I wanted to use all Pearl Drum parts on the Pearl Bass Drum stand on which the parts go but am finding out that it is not worth it.

I will never purchase anything from Sam Ash again. That goes for the large purchases I usually make of PA gear, cymbals, guitars and accessories, microphones, drums and drum accessories. I will go out of my way and pay more elsewhere. They don't deserve my business. They certainly haven't earned it.< /review>< Time>
